verbose_text: Dr. Oehninger 's comments about the " limited number of studies showing that SDF levels can predict the likelihood of natural pregnancy and that higher SDF levels are associated with lower intrauterine insemination (IUI) pregnancy rates, and with lower embryo quality and pregnancy rates in the in vitro fertilization (IVF)/intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI) scenario " are valid but deserve to be viewed in a correct perspective.
